<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,654,2019]" box="[151,452,654,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,299,654,679]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Description:</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[306,415,654,678]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Holotype</typeStatus>
: Ƥ.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,654,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Body length 
<quantity box="[351,437,690,714]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
. Pale yellow brown; ocellar spot, obscure spot on postocellar area (Fig. 
<number box="[1293,1309,690,714]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
b), apex of mandible, lateral stripe on pronotum, outer side of propleuron, elliptical spot on prescutum, one large elongated spot connected to one small round spot on each lobe of scutum, mesopostnotum largely, small spot near cenchrus, a pair of small spots on posterior part of metapostnotum, ventral side of mesepisternum, a stripe on posterior margin of mesepimeron (Fig. 
<number box="[729,745,834,858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
c), a pair of broad maculae on posterior halves of abdominal tergites 
<number box="[291,334,870,894]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="1.0">1–8</number>
and apical sheath black; ventral parts of abdominal tergites entirely yellow brown (Fig. 
<number box="[1388,1404,870,894]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
d); distance between two black maculae on each tergite longer than diameter of middle ocellus, spots on tergite 
<number box="[151,166,942,966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
very small. Legs pale yellow, apical 
<number box="[632,669,942,966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.3">0.3</number>
of hind femur, apical 
<number box="[951,1003,942,966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.25">0.25</number>
of hind tibia black. Antenna black brown, basal 
<number box="[310,325,978,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
or 
<number box="[364,379,978,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
antennomeres paler. Body hairs silver. Wings hyaline, base and apex of vein C, basal 
<number box="[1399,1436,978,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.4">0.4</number>
of stigma pale brown, apical 
<number box="[495,532,1014,1038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.6">0.6</number>
of stigma and other veins blackish brown (Fig. 
<number box="[1100,1117,1014,1038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,654,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Clypeus sparsely punctured; postocellar area minutely and sparsely punctured, head otherwise polished, shiny; mesonotum scarcely and minutely punctured, posterior half of mesoscutellum and posttergite with some larger punctures; metanotum strongly shiny; mesepisternum minutely and sparsely punctured, interspaces between punctures very broad, polished; metapleuron finely microsculptured; all abdominal tergites finely microsculptured, with some shallow and indistinct punctures.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,654,2019]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Anterior margin of labrum roundly protruding, anterior margin of clypeus deeply incised to 
<number box="[1369,1422,1230,1254]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.65">0.65</number>
× clypeus length (Fig. 
<number box="[393,410,1266,1290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
e); malar space as long as radius of middle ocellus; POL: OOL: OCL = 
<number box="[1251,1284,1266,1290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="13.0">13</number>
: 
<number box="[1296,1330,1266,1290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="22.0">22</number>
: 
<number box="[1340,1373,1266,1290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="27.0">27</number>
; postocellar area weakly elevated, as long as wide, lateral furrows feebly curved, slightly convergent toward posterior margin of head; head behind eyes in dorsal view clearly shorter than eye (
<number box="[1104,1122,1338,1362]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number box="[1134,1166,1338,1362]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="14.0">14</number>
), lateral sides straight, parallel (Fig. 
<number box="[314,330,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
b). Relative length of antennomeres about 
<number box="[840,858,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="8.0">8</number>
: 
<number box="[872,891,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<number box="[904,937,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="15.0">15</number>
: 
<number box="[950,983,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="12.0">12</number>
: 
<number box="[996,1029,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="10.0">10</number>
: 
<number box="[1043,1061,1375,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="7.0">7</number>
: 
<number box="[1075,1093,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="6.0">6</number>
: 
<number box="[1106,1124,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
: 
<number box="[1138,1156,1374,1398]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="6.0">6</number>
. Mesoscutellum roundly elevated, posterior slope shorter than anterior slope; distance between cenchri 
<number box="[1063,1098,1410,1434]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.6">1.6</number>
× longest axis of a cenchrus; mesepisternum indistinctly elevated. 
<collectingCountry box="[591,650,1446,1470]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Hind</collectingCountry>
basitarsus as long as tarsomeres 
<number box="[1041,1084,1446,1470]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
together; claw with inner tooth slightly shorter than outer tooth. Vein R+M in forewing as long as half length of free sector of Sc, lower outer corner of cell 
<number box="[315,329,1518,1542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
Rs weakly extended, vein 
<number box="[638,652,1518,1542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
r joining cell 
<number box="[811,825,1518,1542]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
Rs at about middle. Petiole of anal cell in hind wing 
<number box="[151,203,1554,1578]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="0.25">0.25</number>
× length of vein cu-a. Ovipositor sheath as long as metabasitarsus, apical sheath as long as basal plate, lateral view as in Fig. 
<number box="[424,440,1590,1614]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
f; apical sheath about 
<number box="[706,720,1590,1614]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
× as wide as cercus in dorsal view, setae on lateral sides of sheath short, hardly curved. Lancet with 
<number box="[644,673,1629,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="18.0">18</number>
serrulae, membrane between 
<number box="[1034,1049,1629,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="8.0">8</number>
th and 
<number box="[1122,1137,1629,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="9.0">9</number>
th serrulae slightly longer than width of a serrula, 
<number box="[444,458,1668,1692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
th– 
<number box="[486,499,1669,1692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="7.0">7</number>
th serrulae as in Fig. 
<quantity box="[750,782,1668,1692]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
, each with 
<number box="[922,937,1668,1692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="6.0">6</number>
large subbasal teeth at about same level; 
<number box="[151,179,1707,1731]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="11.0">11</number>
th– 
<number box="[208,234,1707,1731]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="13.0">13</number>
th serrulae as in Fig. 
<number box="[459,474,1707,1731]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2.0">2</number>
h.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,654,2019]" box="[199,394,1743,1767]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,1743,1767]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Male:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
